definitions.definition: An area of decayed vegetation (particularly sphagnum moss ) which forms a wet spongy ground too soft for walking.

subdefinitions.definition: ( wetland science , specifically ) An acidic , chiefly rain - fed ( ombrotrophic ), peat -forming wetland . ( Contrast an alkaline fen , and swamps and marshes . )

definitions.definition: ( figuratively ) Confusion , difficulty , or any other thing or place that impedes progress in the manner of such areas.
( UK , Ireland , Australia and New Zealand , slang ) A place to defecate : originally specifically a latrine or outhouse but now used for any toilet .
( Australia and New Zealand , slang ) An act or instance of defecation .
( US , dialect ) A little elevated spot or clump of earth, roots, and grass, in a marsh or swamp.
